    <briefdescription>
<para>I2C device register helpers — thin layer over port I2C. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Provides convenient register-level access for I2C sensors/peripherals. Eliminates boilerplate for reading/writing 8-bit and 16-bit registers and burst reads.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__I2CDev" kindref="compound">SYN_I2CDev</ref><sp/>bmp280;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__i2c__dev_8h_1a6e3fb90568f865657f88d7821d97f4cc" kindref="member">syn_i2c_dev_init</ref>(&amp;bmp280,<sp/>0,<sp/>0x76);<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>bus<sp/>0,<sp/>addr<sp/>0x76</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/>chip_id<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__i2c__dev_8h_1a40820fe12addc374713c2777d10a2b47" kindref="member">syn_i2c_dev_read8</ref>(&amp;bmp280,<sp/>0xD0);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__i2c__dev_8h_1a2c6af3de0cee542d9f94bcc9fc1efdba" kindref="member">syn_i2c_dev_write8</ref>(&amp;bmp280,<sp/>0xF4,<sp/>0x27);<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>ctrl_meas</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/>burst[6];</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__i2c__dev_8h_1a086656bcb3a634be537c61475089aa7f" kindref="member">syn_i2c_dev_read_burst</ref>(&amp;bmp280,<sp/>0xF7,<sp/>burst,<sp/>6);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
